Comment: I started off as usual with kings pawn opening.
He replied mirror opening
I follow up with my favorite c4...always looking to take on f-7 so the king can't castle to throw off my opponent.
He brings out his knight
I get ready trade to move my bishop to g5 to take his knight to weaken his king.
Looks like he's setting up a simple king's indian defense.
Again he doesn't know that I really want his knight in my pocket. I prepare to take.
He makes questionable move.
I counter...and at the same time I prepare to move my queen to c2 for a second check on the king after the bishop checks him on f7.
He retreats
Here is where I make my move and check his king to take him out of position and throw him off.
He does the obvious.
Second check goes as planned.
He brings his king back home.
This is where the noob comes out of me....There is no reason for this move. I was hoping to take the pawn on c5 at the same time checking his king but didn't see the defending knight...stupid I know!
Looks like he's bringing out the bishop to protect his knight.
I bring out my knight in hopes to castle soon and protect the bishop and for center control.
He does what is expected and pushes up one of his pawns to d6
I push up my pawn for center control.
He takes my pawn on d4
